	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The game probably doesn't fully validate the save game data. It might claim to have 100 hearts and cause the heart-drawing routine to corrupt other things, or similar. This must have always been a worry on those battery-RAM cartridges, that the data would become corrupt in a way that rendered the cartridge unusable until it were physically opened and the battery removed for a while. I imagine checksums were there for this reason, rather than preventing cheating.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


